-step\nregularization algorithm is devised to minimize the errors stemming from the\ninexact geometric reconstruction and FOD recovery. The performance of the\ninverse solution is illustrated by a set of numerical experiments where a\ncylindrical fracture, endowed with two example patterns of specific stiffness\ncoefficients, is illuminated by plane waves and reconstructed in terms of its\ngeometry and heterogeneous (dissipative) contact condition.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 23 Oct 2016 23:53:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-01-11"}
